04/03/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey and Germany signed an agreement Monday (3 March) on co-operation in the fight against organised crime, particularly terrorism and trafficking.
German Interior Minister Otto Schily, on a visit to Ankara, did the honours.
According to his Turkish counterpart, Abdulkadir Aksu, the agreement increases opportunities for international co-operation in the prevention of illegal activities.
(Anadolou Agency - 03/03/03)
